                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/759: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-08T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 8, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>43. The President has received the following message dated August 5 by telegraph
                    from the Emperor: “We desire to express our thanks for your statement to the
                    press on August 1st. Ethiopia has not ceased since beginning to seek peaceful
                    settlement and especially <pb facs="0836" n="734" xml:id="pg_734"/> appreciates
                    the support of the Government and people of the United States in the cause of
                    peace.”</p>
                <p>The President desires you to acknowledge orally the receipt of the Emperor’s
                    message and to convey to him an appropriate expression of the President’s
                    appreciation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
